In my advising session with DeNero, he said they cover pretty different material (both still related to machine learning) and it's totally fine to take 100 and then 189. If I recall correctly, 189 is more about how to use data once you have it in a clean format (more math based), and 100 is more about what data to choose and getting raw data into that clean format. 

Also beware of 170's heavy workload in combination with 61C's ungodly amount of easy material would make 189 a horrible decision, especially so when you have so much time as a freshman. You may want to consider alternatives in the statistics department like 134.

Hey! I am currently a freshman, intended cs, thinking about taking Data 100 or CS61C next Fall, in combination with CS170. I'm planning to declare CS this summer and wondering what would be a good class to follow up on the Data 100 material. Is there any benefit of taking Data 100 if i am planning to do CS189 later on anyways? I'm hoping to also major in data science after the official requirements get released.
